
Useful Commands for Ubuntu server

1.  Search any running process
  $ ps -ef |grep process_name

2. Run a background script using nohup
  Example running a jar file using nohup.
  $ nohup java -jar file_name.jar &
  Same can be done with python and other scripts
  
  See nohup output log
  $ tail -f nohup.out
  
3.  Make a file executatble or change permission
  $ chmod +x filename.sh
  
4. To run your script :
./script-name-here.sh
